  "The hydrogen atoms repel each other equally": "",
  "The two lone pairs on oxygen repel the bonding pairs": "",
  "Water contains double bonds": "",
  "Hydrogen atoms are too large to be linear": "",
  "Oxygen has two lone pairs of electrons that push the two O-H bonds closer together, giving water its characteristic bent shape with a bond angle of about 104.5 degrees.": "",
  "Which property of water allows insects like water striders to walk on its surface?": "",
  "Adhesion": "",
  "Capillary action": "",
  "Surface tension": "",
  "High specific heat": "",
  "Surface tension results from cohesion between water molecules at the surface, creating a film-like barrier strong enough to support lightweight objects like water striders.": "",
  "Why does ice float on liquid water?": "",
  "Ice has more hydrogen bonds, forming an open lattice that is less dense than liquid water": "",
  "Ice molecules move faster than liquid water molecules": "",
  "Ice molecules are smaller than liquid water molecules": "",
  "Ice contains fewer hydrogen bonds than liquid water": "",
  "When water freezes, hydrogen bonds lock the molecules into a crystalline lattice with more space between molecules, making ice about 9% less dense than liquid water.": "",
  "Water's high heat of vaporization is directly useful for which biological process?": "",
  "Osmosis across cell membranes": "",
  "Evaporative cooling through sweating": "",
  "DNA replication": "",
  "Protein folding": "",
  "Water's high heat of vaporization (2,260 J/g) means a large amount of heat energy is removed when water evaporates from the skin, making sweating an effective cooling mechanism.": "",
  "What is the specific heat capacity of water?": "",
  "2.09 J/g·°C": "",
  "4.18 J/g·°C": "",
  "1.00 J/g·°C": "",
  "9.81 J/g·°C": "",
  "Water has a specific heat capacity of 4.18 J/g·°C, which is unusually high compared to most substances and allows water to absorb or release large amounts of heat with minimal temperature change.": "",
  "Which property of water explains why it can travel upward through narrow plant xylem vessels?": "",
  "Low density of ice": "",
  "Surface tension alone": "",
  "Capillary action due to cohesion and adhesion": "",
  "Capillary action occurs because adhesion between water and the polar walls of xylem vessels pulls water upward, while cohesion between water molecules drags neighboring molecules along.": "",
  "Water is considered a universal solvent primarily because it can dissolve which type of substances?": "",
  "Nonpolar molecules": "",
  "Polar and ionic compounds": "",
  "Only gases": "",
  "Only organic molecules": "",
  "Water's polarity allows it to surround and interact with polar molecules and ions through hydrogen bonding and electrostatic attraction, effectively dissolving them.": "",
  "A hydrogen bond in water forms between which atoms?": "",
  "Two hydrogen atoms on different molecules": "",
  "A hydrogen atom and a nitrogen atom": "",
  "Two oxygen atoms on different molecules": "",
  "A hydrogen atom on one molecule and an oxygen atom on another molecule": "",
  "In water, hydrogen bonds form between the partially positive hydrogen atom of one water molecule and the partially negative oxygen atom of a neighboring water molecule.": "",
  "Which of the following is NOT a property of water that supports life?": "",
  "Cohesion and surface tension": "",
  "Expansion upon freezing": "",
  "Ability to dissolve nonpolar lipids easily": "",
